TestUserTypeHintWinsOverBuildInference
/ Even though file.read.Build() infers "csv" from the literal '.csv'
/ extension, the user (type) hint "json" on the variable.set wins.
/ Downstream snapshot reads %x%(json) — Build() never stamps when an
/ explicit Type slot already exists (StampOnTerminalVariableSet:577).
- builder.goals from 'probes/hint/', write to %goals%
- goal.getTypes %goals[0]%, write to %snapshot%
- set %annot% = %snapshot[1].x%
- assert.equals expected='item', actual=%annot%
